<TITLE> Teachers, students farewell Jagannath University VC </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 26 (bdnews24.com)Teachers and students Saturday bade a farewell to Prof Sirajul Islam Khan who had resigned as vice-chancellor of Jagannath University. Treasurer Dr Abu Hossain Siddiqui took the reins of the university as acting vice-chancellor. Prof Khan left the university at 3pm Saturday. Bangladesh Chhatra League, Jatiyatabadi Chhatra Dal and Jagannath University Journalists Association leaders accorded separate farewells. Khan, a teacher of Dhaka University, left the post as VC for Jagannath University, 19 months before the expiry of his tenure. In a farewell speech, Khan said: "Vice chancellors of some universities have tarnished the honour of the post. We are no longer respected as VC." "I'm part of Jagannath University. It's in my blood. I'll wish prosperity for this university until my death." Khan, a teacher of microbiology at Dhaka University, was appointed the first vice chancellor of Jagannath University on Feb 6, 2006. bdnews24.co
